"{\"uid\": \"www.accountancyage.com.-2016-07-04-post-brexit-britain-open-for-business-as-osborne-to-slash-corporate-tax-rate-\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"BRITAIN will soon boast the lowest corporation tax rate of any major economy, after chancellor George Osborne revealed plans to slash the rate from 20% to less than 15%.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 169, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 95, \"end\": 109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Osborne\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4213415060563288e-40, \"text\": \"George Osborne\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Osborne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Osborne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In an interview with the Financial Times, the chancellor said the cuts were part of a plan to galvanise the economy and woo businesses that may be unsure of their British allegiances following Brexit.\", \"from\": 171, \"to\": 371, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 196, \"end\": 211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Financial_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.85841603240768e-21, \"text\": \"Financial Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Financial_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Financial_Times\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Super competitive economy'  The move would see Britain possess a corporation tax rate just 2.5% higher than Ireland's, where a number of multinational corporations, including Facebook and Google, base their European operations.\", \"from\": 373, \"to\": 601, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In his first interview since 52% of the referendum voted to leave the EU, Osborne stated that he wanted to create a \\\"super competitive economy\\\" through low taxes and by attracting further global investment, particularly from China.\", \"from\": 603, \"to\": 834, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We must focus on the horizon and the journey ahead and make the most of the hand we have been dealt,\\\" said Osborne, whose new five-point plan to stimulate the economy includes furthering Chinese investment; guaranteeing support for bank lending; an increase in efforts to invest in the Northern powerhouse; and maintaining the UK's fiscal credibility.\", \"from\": 836, \"to\": 1188, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Osborne also urged the Bank of England to use its powers to avoid \\\"a contraction of credit in the economy\\\".\", \"from\": 1190, \"to\": 1297, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the last Budget, Osborne announced that corporation tax would be reduced to 17% by 2020, but the plans to reduce the tax even further has prompted worrying calls from the OECD.\", \"from\": 1299, \"to\": 1478, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"UK a tax haven?\", \"from\": 1480, \"to\": 1495, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The negative impact of the Brexit on UK competitiveness may push the UK to be even more aggressive in its tax offer,\\\" said Pascal Saint-Amans, the OECD's head of tax in an internal memo that was brought to light by Reuters.\", \"from\": 1497, \"to\": 1721, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"A further step in that direction would really turn the UK into a tax haven type of economy,\\\" he added.\", \"from\": 1723, \"to\": 1826, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In January, French MEP Eva Joly told BBC Radio 4's Today programme that the UK is \\\"preparing itself to become a tax haven\\\" for multinationals, in a reaction to Google's \\u00a3130m agreement with HMRC over unpaid back taxes.\", \"from\": 1828, \"to\": 2046, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Share\", \"from\": 2048, \"to\": 2053, \"entities\": []}]}"